<Content>Adventures in Gansta-Land My friend came to Dallas for work and I told her about this place which I had read about. She got a reservation and we decided to meet for dinner at the hotel on her second night.I was waiting out front of the hotel restaurant (overlooking a Dollar General Store) watching for my friend to walk down the hill from the hotel and there was this group of crazy looking gangster types walking down Ft Worth Ave (very bad area) they were just hanging around, drinking out of paper bags. They were scary and I just froze as they approached. I was not sure whether to run or scream but I just stepped backward towards the door. One of the guys rushed towards me and got about 10 feet from me so fast. He thought it was hilarious. Tattoos on the face and neck and visibly wasted. He walked away and threw down his paper bag/bottle. I managed to duck into the restaurant, which was really pretty. But I was still worried about my friend because these people were just walking around out there and hollering at the other 鈥榞anstas鈥?driving down the street. She made it safely. Dinner was ok but service was painfully slow and they were out of the entr茅e I ordered. I only found out they ran out after waiting for my meal. They were a little unorganized in general. Waitstaff was nice.So I went back up the hill with her to see her room. Cute bungalow that was correctly represented on the website.The only problem is that it backs up to some big construction site and they start working early each morning.Later I walked back down to the parking lot and hurried into my car. My heart was pounding. It is just a dangerous area. It did not help that on my way out I commented to an employee and they just chuckled and said that the area IS bad and they see a lot of crazy stuff.The parking lot is mostly dirt and concrete chunks. It all seems so out of place.I got out of the parking lot and headed towards the highway and what the鈥?a freakin鈥?sheriff is behind me with his lights on. I was worried but I had done nothing.He ID鈥檇 me and was friendly enough. We chatted for a few minutes and he said that they check a lot of people in the area because of 鈥榩roblems鈥? He thought I was someone who possibly just stole a car.OK. Well I got the heck out there!Bottom line, I think the place is kind of cute but I just don鈥檛 know if it is worth risking my life to go there at this time. It looks like it will be gentrified in a year or two. Loads of construction and lots of space for sale. Maybe I will check it out again in 2010.Until then I will recommend that out of town friends stay in the uptown area. 
